  "market_context": "Bullish dollar day with DXY showing sweep and candle 2 closure; GBPUSD exhibited strong bearish expansion while EURUSD did not, prompting relative strength analysis via EURGBP.",
  "key_observation": "EURGBP showed a bearish daily candle closing near its low, indicating euro weaker than pound—making EURUSD the optimal short among foreign currencies against a bullish dollar.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst confirmed dollar bullish bias using DXY 1H chart showing a sweep followed by candle 2 closure.",
    "Step 2: Analyst compared GBPUSD and EURUSD price action on daily charts, noting GBPUSD had strong bearish expansion while EURUSD did not.",
    "Step 3: Analyst examined EURGBP daily chart and observed a bearish candle closing near its low, signaling euro weakness relative to pound.",
    "Step 4: Analyst concluded that with bullish dollar and bearish EURGBP, EURUSD is the most bearish foreign currency and thus the preferred short.",
    "Step 5: Analyst verified EURUSD daily chart showed bearish closure, then dropped to 1H fractal model to identify continuation lower after consolidation high sweep."
  ],
  "outcome": "Short EURUSD taken after consolidation high sweep and fractal model confirmation; price continued lower through prior lows.",
  "lessons": "Relative strength analysis across correlated pairs (e.g., EURGBP) is critical to select the strongest/weakness asset within a directional bias; trading the wrong asset despite correct macro view leads to missed expansions.",
